==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hemostatic
<hw>Hem`o*stat"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hemo-</ets> + Gr. <grk>statiko`s</grk> causing to stand, fr.
<?/ to stand.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Of or relating
to stagnation of the blood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Serving to arrest hemorrhage; styptic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hemostatic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hemostatic
<hw>Hem`o*stat"ic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A medicine or application to
arrest hemorrhage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hemothorax</ent>⟦br⟧
